.START 

Thomas M. Hyatt, vice president, business development, with Northern Telecom Inc., was elected chief financial officer and executive vice president, finance and administration, of this telecommunications company.
Mr. Hyatt replaces Ronald Plunkett, who resigned to pursue other opportunities.
Allan L. Rayfield, a consultant for telecommunications and environmental concerns and previously a director of GTE Corp., and Jeffrey Hanft, founder, chairman and chief executive officer of People's Telephone Co., were named to the board, filling a vacancy and increasing the board's size to 11 from 10.
The vacancy was created when former Texas Gov. Mark White resigned to pursue other opportunities. 

